abstract: The erroneous report involving Donald Trump Jr. and WikiLeaks came at a time when the media faces public skepticism and frequent criticism from the White House.
snippet: The erroneous report involving Donald Trump Jr. and WikiLeaks came at a time when the media faces public skepticism and frequent criticism from the White House.
lead_paragraph: CNN on Friday corrected an erroneous report that Donald Trump Jr. had received advance notice from the anti-secrecy group WikiLeaks about a trove of hacked documents that it planned to release during last year’s presidential campaign.

abstract: The newly elected Nassau County executive says her drive to see how the world works has driven her journalistic and political career.
snippet: The newly elected Nassau County executive says her drive to see how the world works has driven her journalistic and political career.
lead_paragraph: BALDWIN, N.Y. — It may seem odd that for someone whose name has graced the byline of more than 900 articles in two New York City tabloids, one of Laura Curran’s first acts as Nassau County executive will effectively strip away credit for her new title.

abstract: The tax bills moving through Congress could hobble the United States’ renewable energy industry because of provisions that scale back incentives for wind and solar power.
snippet: The tax bills moving through Congress could hobble the United States’ renewable energy industry because of provisions that scale back incentives for wind and solar power.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Republican tax bills moving through Congress could significantly hobble the United States’ renewable energy industry because of a series of provisions that scale back incentives for wind and solar power while bolstering older energy sources like oil and gas production.

abstract: New York City voters have made clear over the years that two terms are enough for city officials, but City Council members are considering a third.
snippet: New York City voters have made clear over the years that two terms are enough for city officials, but City Council members are considering a third.
lead_paragraph: Horror film devotees are well acquainted with Chucky, the doll possessed by an evil spirit that refuses to die. It’s kind of like the issue of easing term limits for New York City elected officials. Just when you thought it would be seen no more, it springs once again to life. And now it’s b-a-a-ack.
